Not by soloing. &quot;<br>
<br>
I dont know about clerics...but druids found a way to do it.  Nec found a way to do it.  Wiz found a way to do it. Mage found a way to do it.  SK found a way to do it.  Bard found a way to do it.  (i think you get the point).  Maybe clerics will find a way to do it someday.  The fact is--cleric is the only 'required' class for group for 3 expansions, (Even chanter can be replaced by bard.) all other classes have to deal with at one time or another--'what to do now? i can't get a group'.<br>
<br>
&quot;Considering there are 3 times as many druids than clerics we will be hard pressed to find a group. IF I can get there first and OOC at the same time or before a druid, this is where the 3X as many comes into play.&quot;<br>
<br>
You would think there are a lot of druids. But fact is most of them are port-bot or plvl-bot.  You would be supprised if you find out how many 'real' high lvl druid are left.<br>
<br>
&quot;If druids want to group why didnt they go make a class that was based on grouping. Or toss us some nukes so we can take your place in XP soloing, since you will be taking ours in grouping.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Read my post above.  How do you feel if i advise you to start a druid if you want to group?  Why do i have to start another class just so i can group? This is a MMORPG!!!<br>
<br>
&quot;Though druids do need something, so I'm glad to see the bone thrown. Im just scared Ill be back to XP'ing with guild only&quot;<br>
